Here's a basic example of a media query for mobile devices:

```
@media only screen and (max-width: 768px) {
  /* styles for mobile devices */
}
```

This media query will apply the styles within the curly brackets to any device with a screen width of 768px or less. Common values for mobile devices include:

* 360px
* 414px (iPhone 6 and 6 Plus)
* 480px
* 576px
* 640px
* 720px
* 768px

You can adjust the value to suit your needs.

If you want to apply styles to all mobile devices, you can use the following media query:

```
@media only screen and (max-width: 1024px) {
  /* styles for mobile devices */
}
```

This will apply the styles to devices with a maximum screen width of 1024px, which is roughly the width of a standard tablet.

Note that you can also use other devices like tablets, desktops, or laptops by using the following media queries:

```
@media only screen and (max-width: 1024px) and (orientation: portrait) {
  /* styles for portrait tablets */
}

@media only screen and (max-width: 1024px) and (orientation: landscape) {
  /* styles for landscape tablets */
}
```

These media queries will apply the styles to the specified device types.

